# Copy this file to .env (in this same directory) and fill in the paths
# that apply to your setup. .env is gitignored -- it's meant to hold
# machine-specific paths, not something to commit.
#
# Both of these are optional. If your ComfyUI / venv / this project are
# laid out as three sibling folders (the original assumed layout), you
# don't need this file at all -- auto-detection already handles that case.
# Use this when your layout is different, or you just want to be explicit.
#
# Real environment variables (e.g. `export COMFY_DIR=...` in your shell,
# or `COMFY_DIR=... ./run_server.sh`) always take precedence over these
# values -- .env only fills in whatever isn't already set.

# Path to your ComfyUI installation.
# COMFY_DIR=/path/to/ComfyUI

# Path to the python interpreter inside your venv (the one with torch,
# comfy's own dependencies, etc. already installed). Used both to launch
# the server itself (run_server.sh) and, internally, to launch each
# training subprocess.
# VENV_PYTHON=/path/to/venv/bin/python
